Subject: [PATCH] navbar: candidate avatar, PWA-based marketplace/feed split,
 mobile back button

- Add shared useIsPwa hook (display-mode: standalone detection),
  dedupe the copy that lived in CandidateMobileNav
- Navbar: logo now routes to the marketplace for web (any device),
  and to /candidate/home only when running as an installed PWA
  (was previously keyed off mobile breakpoint, which conflated
  'small screen' with 'installed app')
- Navbar: show the candidate's avatar_url as a circular image in
  the profile pill/menu item instead of a generic profile icon+label
  when one is set, falling back to the icon otherwise
- Home: PWA + signed-in candidate now redirects straight to
  /candidate/home instead of the marketplace landing
- CandidateDashboard: add a mobile-only 'Back to jobs' button at the
  top of the page linking to /jobs, since there was previously no
  way back to the marketplace from here on mobile web
